edge file incorrectly merges these separate sections together into s3. Looking at the heading patterns, I can see there are more headings in the full file than what's visible in this excerpt. The `--------` and `=====` patterns appear multiple times for tags like select, password, and text, suggesting a consistent structure for those sections. Since the automated check found 9 headings but only 7 are shown here, there are 2 additional headings elsewhere in the document that I'm not seeing.\n\nNow I'm checking the hints completeness for the Encryptor section—I can see \"Encryptor,\" \"hiddenEncryptor,\" and \"AES 128bit\" are all accounted for, though the list appears to cut off mid-item. Now I'm checking the s2 hints for the decryption processing layer, confirming that the Nablarch tag handler and hidden parameter decryption are accounted for along with hash validation. Moving into s3, I'm verifying the confirmation page tag implementation covers text rendering, scope search ordering, and input data restoration, though some specific variable examples aren't critical to the overall structure.\n\nFor s4, the password masking and replacement character handling are present in the WebView_PasswordTag implementation. In s5, I'm seeing the select tag covers choice output and br tag delimiters, though the element label and value property attributes from the example code aren't explicitly listed as separate hints. Now I'm starting to verify whether any of these components might be fabricated or if they're all grounded in the actual framework. Checking the other claims now — the default encryption is AES with 128-bit keys, which matches the source documentation. For the formatting options, the default is indeed br tag separation with the ability to switch to div, ul, ol, or space delimiters. And I need to look more carefully at what the knowledge file actually calls section s3.\n\nThe s3 section is titled \"入力データの復元\" but it actually contains both that section and the entire \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" section including the textタグ output example — so the title doesn't accurately reflect the merged content. This is a V3 section issue where the index lists s3 with just \"入力データの復元\" as the title, but the actual content spans both topics, and while the index does reference \"WebView_ConfirmationPageTag\" for s3, the separate \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" section isn't listed as its own entry.\n\nI'm also noticing that V4 has a hints_missing issue where s5 is lacking \"elementLabelProperty\" and \"elementValueProperty\" — both key attributes shown in the example. The automated warning about section count being 5 versus 9 source headings suggests at least 2 headings are merged, and checking against the V3 rule about h2 content size would help clarify whether this merge is justified. Looking at the RST heading structure, both \"入力データの復元\" and \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" use the same `=====` format, placing them at the same hierarchical level rather than one being nested under the other. The s3 section merges these three source headings into roughly 1000+ characters, and since \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" contains sub-sections marked with `--------`, this could potentially trigger the V3 rule about h2 sections with h3 children not being split.\n\nI should flag this as a V3 section_issue for merging distinct source sections that should arguably be separate. Now I'm checking what content might have been omitted—the screen transition reference with request IDs appears to be just a diagram reference, but the note about writeタグ being output-only and excluded from search parameters is captured in the knowledge file.\n\nLooking at the confirmation screen output section, the screen image references were correctly omitted as navigation elements, and the textタグ output examples were properly merged into s3. The content preservation looks solid overall.\n\nSo my findings are: first, s3 combines three separate source sections (\"入力データの復元\", \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\", and \"textタグの出力例\") that exceed the character threshold when merged, and the knowledge file's index doesn't adequately reflect the confirmation page output topic. Second, s5 is missing the elementLabelProperty and elementValueProperty attributes that appear in the source.\n\nWait, let me reconsider the first issue against the V3 rule. The rule flags h2 sections with 2000+ characters that have h3 subsections but aren't split in the knowledge file. \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" is an h-level section with subsections like \"textタグの出力例\", and the merged content in s3 likely exceeds 2000 characters. Both \"入力データの復元\" and \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" are at the same heading level, yet the knowledge file only has s3 titled \"入力データの復元\" covering both sections.\n\nThe real problem is that \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" should either be its own section or a subsection, but instead it's merged under s3. I'll report this as a section_issue. I also notice that \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" has no separate index entry—the hints for \"confirmationPage\" and \"WebView_ConfirmationPageTag\" are buried in s3, but the section title itself isn't represented in the index.\n\nFor my final report, I'm documenting two findings: first, the section_issue where \"入力項目の確認画面用の出力\" is improperly merged with \"入力データの復元\" in s3, likely exceeding the character threshold with its h3-level sub-sections. Second, s5 is missing `elementLabelProperty` and `elementValueProperty` as hints—these are key attribute names in the select tag's JSP example.\n\nLet me go back and double-check s1 against the original spec. \"ウィンドウスコープの値\" is listed as one of the encrypted data items, and I need to verify it's actually present in the knowledge file. I've identified two minor issues: the s3 section incorrectly merges two same-level source sections with one subsection, and s5 is missing the elementLabelProperty and elementValueProperty hints.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21645,"cache_read_input_tokens":29807,"cache_creat